    "abstract": "A behavioural method is described for the assessment of depth perception\\nof kittens. Measurement is made of the smallest separation in depth\\nthat can be discriminated between two adjacent stimuli under both\\nmonocular and binocular viewing conditions. Normal animals can discriminate\\nmuch smaller separations in depth when using two eyes than with monocular\\nviewing, implying the presence of a cue to depth that is uniquely\\navailable with binocular viewing. The test provides a quick and reliable\\nway of screening animals for stereopsis."
